    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>3 lbs goat paya (hoof), cleaned and cut</li>
            <li>2 large onions, finely sliced</li>
            <li>4 tomatoes, chopped</li>
            <li>1/4 cup ginger-garlic paste</li>
            <li>1/4 cup yogurt</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons red chili powder</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon turmeric powder</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon garam masala</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon coriander powder</li>
            <li>1 cinnamon stick</li>
            <li>4 green cardamom pods</li>
            <li>4 cloves</li>
            <li>2 bay leaves</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
            <li>4 tablespoons vegetable oil</li>
            <li>Fresh coriander leaves for garnish</li>
            <li>Chopped ginger for garnish</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>nonveg</li>
            <li>indian</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Wash and clean goat paya thoroughly. Boil in a large pot of water until the paya is tender. Discard the water and set aside.</li>
            <li>In a separate pan, heat vegetable oil. Add sliced onions and sauté until golden brown.</li>
            <li>Add ginger-garlic paste and sauté until the raw smell disappears.</li>
            <li>Add chopped tomatoes, red chili powder, turmeric powder, garam masala, and coriander powder. Cook until the tomatoes are soft and the oil separates.</li>
            <li>Add boiled goat paya to the masala mixture. Mix well.</li>
            <li>In a spice bag or muslin cloth, tie cinnamon stick, cardamom pods, cloves, and bay leaves. Add this bag to the curry.</li>
            <li>Add yogurt and salt. Simmer on low heat until the curry thickens and the flavors meld together.</li>
            <li>Garnish with fresh coriander leaves and chopped ginger.</li>
            <li>Serve hot with naan or steamed rice.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your hearty Goat Paya Curry!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>
